						               													<description>The Megs is a cyberpunk two player competitive card game for players aged 14+ where cards positioning is central and, with highly-thematic effects, will generate  brain-burning situations.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In The Megs, you will use colourful characters called Operators to wage corporate war against an enemy Megacorporation. Positioning your Operators and activating their skills, you will try to complete extremely risky missions like assassinating a high-ranking enemy Operative or smearing high-visibility opponents in the infamy of a sex scandal but, most of all, you will deploy your best and slyest hackers to steal precious data from your opponent!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Played in three rounds called Operations or &amp;ldquo;Ops&amp;rdquo; over the course of 30 to 45 minutes, the game is playable on a 13 per 18 inches (33/45 cm) table and meant to offer the depth and challenge of bigger games with the option of reducing it to a shirt pocket-friendly size.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The mechanics aim at generating puzzle-like situations, bluff, double-guessing, and mind-bending domino-effect while introducing edgy characters and tense situations that will immerse the players into our special breed of the Noir Sci-fi genre that is cyberpunk.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Including high-tech assassins, vicious cyber-tox, mad salary-men, ruthless gangs of enhanced Yakuzas, mysterious shamans of the virtual world, terrorists from high-tech death cults and lethally sexy Black Widows, The Megs is made into a dark and daring world thanks to the outstanding art of genius illustrator Ania Kryczkowska (Gloom of Kilforth, Paradise Lost).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
